    {
      "text": "A 52 y/o male has recurrent pain and swelling in the left lower jaw, worsening over several months. On examination, there is a significant swelling of the right submandibular gland, but no palpable stone. A CT scan shows an 8 mm stone deep within the submandibular gland, inaccessible by sialendoscopy. What is the best next step in management?",
